commit.message: QueueCommand caused race condition. Fixes #101.
Unnecessary function call removal fixes #89.

vimpc: always use "%s"-style format for printf()-style functions

`ncuses-6.3` added printf-style function attributes and now makes
it easier to catch cases when user input is used in palce of format
string when built with CFLAGS=-Werror=format-security:

    src/window/listwindow.cpp:120:16:
      error: format not a string literal and no format arguments [-Werror=format-security]
      120 |       mvwprintw(window, line, 0, BlankLine.c_str());
          |       ~~~~~~~~~^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Let's wrap all the missing places with "%s" format.

A collection of small library-focused improvements

* Add %y format for year
* Add %N format for zero padded trackn umber
* Add sortalbumdate option to sort albums in the library by date
* Only create "Various Artists" if necessary
* Enable albumformat option
* Fix sorting of albums with multiple disks (was broken before)
Fix tmap for ex commands containing spaces
Check for top directory in dir window. Solves #94

commit.message:
Comply with XDG Base Directory Specification

The specification[1] states that if "$XDG_CONFIG_HOME is either not set or empty,
a default equal to $HOME/.config should be used". Changing the unspecified default
path from `~/.vimpcrc` to search for configuration in the following
order:

	$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/vimpc/vimpcrc
	$HOME/.config/vimpc/vimpcrc
	$HOME/.vimpcrc

Updated documentation to reflect the new location for the config file.

[1] https://specifications.freedesktop.org/basedir-spec/basedir-spec-latest.html
